inlineContent.text: This enumeration takes user A logged into both DeviceA1 and DeviceA2 as an example to illustrate the various multi-device event types and when these events are triggered.

abstract.text: Multi-device event types.
If user A removes a user from the blocklist on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user A deletes a contact on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user A unmutes other group members in DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user A receives another user’s request to join the chat group on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user A requests to join a chat group on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user joined group is disabled, all devices of user A receive the event.
If user A declines another user’s group invitation on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user A accepts a contact invitation on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user A blocks messages from a chat group on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
If user A assigns a group owner on DeviceA1, this event is triggered on DeviceA2.
